## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-115">コンストラクター <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A>によって<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A>プロパティが初期化されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-115">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A> constructor initializes the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-116">識別子は、特定の文法内で一意である必要があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-116">The identifier must be unique within a given grammar.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-117">コンストラクター <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A>は、次<xref:System.FormatException>のような場合にをスローします。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-117">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A> constructor throws a <xref:System.FormatException> in the following circumstances:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-118">`id`は、[拡張マークアップ言語 (xml) 1.0 (5 番目のエディション)](https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/)で定義されている有効な xml 名ではありません。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-118">`id` is not a valid XML name, as defined in [Extensible Markup Language (XML) 1.0 (Fifth Edition)](https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-119">この定義を一昔前するには、有効な XML 名の先頭に文字、アンダースコア (' _ ')、またはコロン (': ') を指定する必要があります。また、0個以上の NameChar 文字 (XML 仕様でも定義されています) を後に付けることができます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-119">To paraphrase this definition, a valid XML name must begin with a letter, an underscore ('_'), or a colon (':') and can be followed by zero or more NameChar characters (also defined in the XML specification).</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-120">`id`は、"NULL" または "VOID" または "ガーベジ" です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-120">`id` is "NULL" or "VOID" or "GARBAGE".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-121">`id`少なくとも1つの無効な規則 ID 文字が含まれています。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-121">`id` contains at least one invalid rule ID character.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-122">これらの文字は '? ' です。、' \* '、' + '&#124;、' '、' ('、')、' ^ '、' $ '、'/'、'; '、'. '、' = '\<、' '、' > '、' ['、'] '、' {'、'\\\\} '、' '、' '、' \t '、' \r '、および ' \n '。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-122">These characters are: '?', '\*', '+', '&#124;', '(', '), '^', '$', '/', ';', '.', '=', '\<', '>', '[', ']', '{', '}', '\\\\', ' ', '\t', '\r', and '\n'.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-123">次の例では、"ワールドカップを獲得した国" という語句を認識する文法を作成し、その後にワールドカップを獲得した国の名前が続きます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-123">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-124">この例では<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> 、と`winnerRule`いう名前のオブジェクトを`WorldCupWinner`作成し<xref:System.String>、その識別子をとして渡します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-124">The example creates a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object named `winnerRule` and passes in the identifier  `WorldCupWinner` as a <xref:System.String>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-125">オブジェクト<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>は、規則によって認識<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>される代替手段を含む新しいオブジェクトの配列で構成されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-125">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object consists of an array of new <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> objects containing alternatives to be recognized by the rule.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"),   
    new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"),   
    new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```

  
  
