## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-141">次の例では、"ワールドカップを獲得した国" という語句を認識する文法を作成し、その後にワールドカップを獲得した国の名前が続きます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-141">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-142">この例では、という`WorldCupWinner`名前のパブリックルールを作成します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-142">The example creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-143">次に、2つ<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>のオブジェクト`ruleEurope` `ruleSAmerica`を作成し、ルール<xref:System.String>識別子<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsElement>にを、オブジェクトを<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>含む配列を渡します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-143">The example then creates two <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objects, `ruleEurope` and  `ruleSAmerica`, passing in a <xref:System.String> for the rule identifier and an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsElement> array containing a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-144">その後、この例では、 `ruleEurope`ルール`ruleSAmerica`との間`WorldCupWinner`にルール参照を追加します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-144">Subsequently, the example adds rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica` from the rule `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  // Create a grammar from an SRGSDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument srgsGrammar = new SrgsDocument ();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule ("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add (new SrgsItem ("A nation that has won the world cup is"));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the grammar and make winnerRule  
  // the root rule of the grammar.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  srgsGrammar.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-145">作成された文法には、次の形式があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-145">The created grammar has the following form.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<grammar version="1.0" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar" root="WorldCupWinner">  
    <rule id="WorldCupWinner" scope="public">  
        <item> A nation that has won the world cup is </item>  
        <one-of>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#EuropeanNations" />  
            </item>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#SouthAmericanNations" />  
            </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="EuropeanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> England </item>  
            <item> France </item>  
            <item> Germany </item>  
            <item> Italy </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="SouthAmericanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> Argentina </item>  
            <item> Brazil </item>  
            <item> Uruguay </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
</grammar>  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-153">通常<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> 、オブジェクトに追加されるのは、、、、およびオブジェクトです。このオブジェクトには、話す人を指定します。 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem></span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-153">Typical additions to an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object include <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>, and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> objects that specify what speakers can say.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-154">有効な rule 要素には、認識可能なテキストまたはルール参照が少なくとも1つ含まれている必要があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-154">A valid rule element must contain at least one piece of recognizable text or one rule reference.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-155">詳細については、「 [SrgsGrammar を使用した文法の作成](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361680(v%3doffice.14))」を参照してください。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-155">See [Create Grammars Using SrgsGrammar](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361680(v%3doffice.14)) for more information.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-156">オブジェクト<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>には、規則<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag>に<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>セマンティック値およびセマンティックキーを追加するオブジェクトとオブジェクトを含めることもできます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-156">An <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object may also contain <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> objects that add semantic values and semantic keys to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-157">音声認識エンジンは、語句を認識すると、セマンティック情報と認識された語句を返します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-157">The speech recognition engine will return the semantic information, as well as the recognized phrase, when it recognizes the phrase.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-158">詳細については、「[セマンティック解釈マークアップ](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361595(v%3doffice.14))」を参照してください。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-158">See [Semantic Interpretation Markup](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361595(v%3doffice.14)) for more information.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-159">次の例では、"ワールドカップを獲得した国" という語句を認識する文法を作成し、その後にワールドカップを獲得した国の名前が続きます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-159">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-160"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>オブジェクトを作成し`winnerRule` 、そのオブジェクトに文字列識別子`WorldCupWinner`を指定すると、 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A>この例では、メソッドを使用して、ルールに "ワールドカップがある国カップ" という文字列を追加します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-160">After creating the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object `winnerRule` and giving it the string identifier `WorldCupWinner`, the example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> method to append the string  "A nation that has won the World Cup is" to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-161">この例では、とと`ruleEurope` `ruleSAmerica`いう2つの追加の規則を作成します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-161">The example then creates two additional rules, `ruleEurope` and  `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-162">この例で<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A>は、メソッドを使用し<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>て、と`WorldCupWinner` `ruleSAmerica`へ`ruleEurope`の規則参照を含む規則にオブジェクトを追加します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-162">Again using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> method, the example appends an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object to the `WorldCupWinner` rule that contains rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
// and set its scope to public.  
SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
// Add the introduction.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
// Create the rule for the European nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
// Create the rule for the South American nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
// Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
// Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
// the root rule of the document.  
document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
document.Root = winnerRule;  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-192">スコープの既定値は`Private`です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-192">The default value for scope is `Private`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-193">プライベートルールをアクティブにできるのは、そのルールが含まれている文法またはルートルールから参照されている別のルールからのルール参照によってのみです。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-193">A private rule can only be activated for recognition by a rule reference from the root rule in its containing grammar or from another rule that is referenced from the root rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-194">プライベートルールが、含んでいる文法のルートルールとして宣言されている場合を除き、外部文法でプライベートルールを参照することはできません。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-194">A private rule cannot be referenced by an external grammar, unless the private rule is declared as the root rule of its containing grammar.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-195">スコープがに`Public` <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>設定され<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>ている場合は、オブジェクトを、含んでいる文法内のオブジェクトからの参照、または外部文法のルールから、認識できるようにアクティブにすることができます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-195">If its scope is set to `Public`, an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object can be activated for recognition by a reference from a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> object in the containing grammar or from a rule in an external grammar.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-196">次の例では、"ワールドカップを獲得した国" という語句を認識する文法を作成し、その後にワールドカップを獲得した国の名前が続きます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-196">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-197">という名前`WorldCupWinner`のパブリックルールを作成し、そのルールのスコープをパブリックに設定します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-197">It creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner` and sets the scope of that rule to Public.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule and set its scope to public.  
SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
// Add the introduction.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
// Create the rule for the European nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
// Create the rule for the South American nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
// Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope)), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica)})));  
  
// Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
// the root rule of the document.  
document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
document.Root = winnerRule;  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f2d8f-198">作成された文法には、次の形式があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f2d8f-198">The created grammar has the following form.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<grammar version="1.0" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar" root="WorldCupWinner">  
    <rule id="WorldCupWinner" scope="public">  
        <item> A nation that has won the world cup is </item>  
        <one-of>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#EuropeanNations" />  
            </item>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#SouthAmericanNations" />  
            </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="EuropeanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> England< /item>  
            <item> France </item>  
            <item> Germany </item>  
            <item> Italy </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="SouthAmericanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> Argentina </item>  
            <item> Brazil </item>  
            <item> Uruguay </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
</grammar>  
```
